SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
-------------------
1. Install dependencies:
      pip install openai psutil flask flask-socketio pandas numpy matplotlib
                  seaborn scikit-learn watchdog gputil py-cpuinfo

2. Set your NVIDIA NIM API key:
      export NIM_API_KEY="your-nvidia-nim-api-key-here"
   Or paste it directly into CONFIG["nim_api_key"] below (not recommended).

3. Place data files for analysis into:
      ./data/inbox/
   Supported formats: .csv, .json, .xlsx, .parquet, .txt, .log

4. Results are written to:
      ./data/results/

5. Logs are written to:
      ./logs/agent.log

6. Start the agent (runs the agent + dashboard):
      python agent.py

7. Access the dashboard from any device on your local network:
      http://<raspberry-pi-ip>:5050

8. To find your device's IP:
      hostname -I

9. The agent runs indefinitely. To stop it gracefully:
      Ctrl+C  (or send SIGTERM)

NOTES:
------
- The agent polls ./data/inbox/ every CONFIG["poll_interval_seconds"] seconds.
- Completed files are moved to ./data/processed/.
- Failed files are moved to ./data/failed/ with an error report.
- Rate limiting is handled internally with exponential backoff — no manual
  throttling is needed for long-running (multi-day) operation.
- GPU/VRAM metrics require an NVIDIA GPU and the 'nvidia-smi' tool installed.
  On Raspberry Pi, VRAM metrics will show N/A gracefully.

================================================================================

THIS TOOL IS INTENDED FOR USE ON A RASPBERRY PI 5

================================================================================
